#   CODE-015: test: source lib helpers in case run.sh

Several test case run.sh scripts re-define helpers that already live in test/lib: mkg (git init+config) is pasted into ~10 cases, head_hex (wtlog last-row sha) into 4, and ref_tip (keeper refs tip) into 3. Source the lib versions instead of re-rolling them.

##  Issues

mkg/head_hex/ref_tip are re-defined in case scripts despite existing in test/lib.

 -  mkg() pasted into ~10 run.sh (get/33, post/23, head/19, …) — already a lib helper.
 -  head_hex() byte-identical in 4 post cases (post/03,04,07 …); lib has it.
 -  ref_tip() re-defined in post/03, put/05,07; identical to lib/branches.sh.

##  Blockers

None; test-only, no build. Ensure lib is sourced before first use in each case.

##  Planned

Delete the local copies; source the lib helper in each affected run.sh.

 -  Repro first (§17): the affected cases still pass via ctest after sourcing lib.
 -  Source lib/*.sh for mkg/head_hex/ref_tip; remove the inline defs.

